comments: Primo (SAS) grabs and pulls McCollum's (NOP) right arm as he gathers, which causes McCollum to lose control of the ball prior to Primo making contact with it.
Primo (SAS) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Hayes (NOP) is already in Johnson's (SAS) path and absorbs the body contact that occurs along the perimeter following the hand-off.
Poeltl (SAS) brings his arm outward and marginal contact occurs with Alvarado's (NOP) right arm as he releases the pass.
Landale (SAS) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Murphy III's (NOP) left arm after the release.
All technical fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Poeltl (SAS) brings his forearm toward Murphy III's (NOP) side and marginal contact occurs as Poeltl turns to roll toward the lane.
Johnson (SAS) is retreating as he moves somewhat laterally toward Alvarado's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs during the drive.

Poeltl (SAS) brings his right hand forward as he pursues the rebound and marginal contact occurs with the side of Alvarado's (NOP) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Murray (SAS) is retreating away from Alvarado (NOP) and absorbs the marginal body contact initiated by Alvarado during the driving shot attempt. Poeltl (SAS) then cleanly blocks the shot thereafter.
Murray (SAS) and McCollum (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Poeltl (SAS) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Murray (SAS) engages and disengages with Alvarado (NOP) as Alvarado sets the screen.
Murray (SAS) is moving forward toward Hayes (NOP) and marginal body contact occurs as Hayes pivots along the perimeter.
Primo (SAS) moves alongside Murphy III's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs during Murphy III's drive.
Hayes (NOP) legally contests Murray's (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Landale (SAS) and Murphy III (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Murphy III (NOP) makes contact to Landale's (SAS) right arm and affects his put-back shot attempt.
Jones (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Landale (SAS) prior to incidental contact occurring with Landale's left arm/shoulder.
Poeltl (SAS) engages and disengages with Jones (NOP) as Jones moves to set the pick.
Jones (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Primo's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Primo (SAS) is jumping to the side of Alvarado (NOP) and would avoid making contact with Alvarado if Alvarado did not shift his body to the side to initiate the marginal contact.
Hayes (NOP) brings his hands toward Landale's (SAS) back and marginal contact occurs after Landale retrieves the rebound.
